[SN]TITLE[SN]
Charlie Edwards lands IBF world title chance on Brook-Golovkin bill

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Britain's Charlie Edwards will fight Johnriel Casimero for the IBF world flyweight title at London's 02 Arena on 10 September.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Edwards, 23, is a former Team GB amateur and has a record of seven wins since turning professional in 2015.
"Many people may think this is too early but that IBF world title is coming home with me," said Edwards.
The fight will feature on the undercard of Kell Brook's middleweight clash with undisputed champion Gennady Golovkin.
